{
  "message": "fuzz(path-encoding-mount): 18 structured seeds across name variants \u00d7 mount options\n\nfuzz_path_encoding_mount drives FrankenFuse's lookup / create / mkdir /\nrename / symlink / readdir / readlink mounted-FS paths against\nadversarial name and target byte streams. Each call site uses\nfuzz_name() to draw one of eight variants per slot (empty, \".\",\n\"..\", leading-slash, 256+ byte oversize, three random-bytes shapes)\nand fuzz_target_bytes() draws six target shapes. Existing 4 ad-hoc\nseeds covered only `dot_components`, `empty_components`,\n`long_components`, and `slash_components` \u2014 never the boundary\nparent inodes, the u32::MAX uid/gid case, or the multi-path mixed\nshapes.\n\nAdds 18 seeds covering:\n\n  Per-variant whole-input shapes:\n  * all-empty (variant 0 in every slot)\n  * all-\".\" (variant 1)\n  * all-\"..\" (variant 2)\n  * all-leading-slash (variant 3) with growing payloads\n  * all-too-long (variant 4: 256+ 'a' bytes \u2014 exceeds MAX_NAME_BYTES)\n  * all-random-short (variant 5)\n\n  Mixed-component shapes:\n  * empty + dot + dotdot + leading-slash mix\n  * dotdot rename pair (lookup=\".\" + rename_name=\"..\"\n    + rename_target=\"/new\" + symlink_target=\"./relative/target\")\n  * empty names with non-empty symlink target\n  * realistic mount path (document.pdf / newfile.txt / subdir /\n    oldname \u2192 newname / shortcut \u2192 ../shared/global.toml)\n\n  Mount option \u00d7 FS option boundaries:\n  * read_only=1 with valid lookup\n  * read_only=1 + all-too-long (compound-error path)\n  * UID / GID = u32::MAX\n  * setuid + sticky modes (top mode bits set)\n  * readdir at non-zero offset\n  * boundary high parent inodes (u8::MAX \u2192 ino=256)\n\n  Security-relevant:\n  * NUL bytes in random names (lookup, leading-NUL, trailing-NUL) \u2014\n    pins the cd559dd \"reject NUL path components\" review fix\n\n  Minimum-size:\n  * empty everything with reduced FS-fuel padding\n\nAll 22 corpus inputs load cleanly with `-runs=0`; coverage rises to\n810 PCs / 991 features.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
